Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu has died from COVID-19 related complications. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Deputy Secretary-General, Jessie Duarte says the country must use the passing of Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu as a reminder that COVID-19 is fatal. Mthembu died on Thursday from COVID-19 related complications. Duarte has cautioned people to remain vigilant. WATCH: ANC briefs media on Mthembu's death "We hope that as we go on in the next couple of days, we will find a way to heal ourselves and to understand that the real issue is we all have to mind the period we are in and that COVID-19 is not playing with anybody," she said. "Unless we take matters into our own hands and we are careful and we wear our masks and social distance and we do not attend gatherings, at all, then we will be losing many more valuable South Africans." Mthembu has been hailed as a life-long champion of freedom and democracy.